CLUSTER TYPES
1. INTERACTIVE CLUSTER [ALL PROPOSE CLUSTER]- 
        - can be used by multiple user
        - used in adhoc analysis, data explonation or development
        - don't use in production as its not cost efficient

2. JOB CLUSTER
        - approximently 50% cheaper
        - terminate afer job completed
        - in databricks workflows [jobs] we use this

3. SERVERLESS 
        - No cluster management by you
        - You don’t create, start, resize, or terminate clusters.
        - Databricks automatically provides compute when you run a query or job. [databricks manage everything]
        
        🔹 How it works
        You run a query / notebook / job
        Databricks automatically allocates compute
        Query runs using optimized engine (Photon)
        Compute shuts down automatically after use
        👉 No idle cost, no manual effort

        ✔ Best for:
        SQL analytics (BI tools like Power BI, Tableau)
        Ad-hoc queries
        Dashboards
        Lightweight ETL jobs

        ❌ Not ideal for:
        Heavy custom Spark tuning
        Long-running complex jobs needing full control
        Low-level cluster configuration needs

