DRIVER NODE AND WORKER NODE
    👉 Think of a cluster like a team:
    Driver node = Manager 🧠
    Worker nodes = Workers 💪

when we run query - 
        driver will 
            1. Understands the query
            2. Breaks it into tasks/partitions
            3. Sends tasks to workers
            -- Only one driver per cluster
        worker will
            1. Process data
            2. Execute tasks sent by driver
            3. Read/write data from storage (ADLS/S3)
            4. Perform transformations
            
    🔹 Inside each worker:
        Has multiple cores
        Runs multiple tasks in parallel
    
    🔹 Example:
        Driver says:
        👉 “Process partition 1, 2, 3…”
        Workers:
        👉 Each worker processes different partitions simultaneously

